main event: A UFO sighting was reported in St. Lawrence, Alaska on November 6, 1954. The observation was of a ground-visual nature, but the report concluded that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
interesting points: The sighting took place in the Bearing Sea Area north of St. Lawrence Bell Village.
The source of light was described as 'Camera sited light'.
The report is part of Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program that investigated unidentified flying objects.
Despite the report, there is no photograph present in the image.
The evaluation concluded that there was insufficient data to assess the sighting.
